<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n26226g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26226g">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26226g"> 226(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> loft (roof)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The chimney, <i>lovver</i>, stands in the room; which name may perhaps be connected with the Scandinavian <i>lyre</i> (Icelandic, ljo&oacute;ri); <i>viz</i>., the smoke-hole in the roof or thatch (<i>thack</i>), out of which in olden times, before houses had regular chimneys and &ldquo;<i>lofts</i>&rdquo; (<mark><i>Dan</i>., Loft; <i>Eng</i>., roof, an upper room</mark>), the smoke (<i>reek</i> or <i>reik</i>, <i>Dan</i>., <font color="green">[81]</font> Ro&ouml;g) left the dark (<i>mirk</i> or <i>murk</i>, <i>Dan</i>., mo&ouml;rk) room. <small> Jens Jacob Asmussen Worsaae, <a name="JJAW1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JJAW1"><cite title="source">An Account of the Danes and Norwegians</cite></a> (1852) 81</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
